
	<h2>KDE 4.0 live CD </h2>

	<p>Thanks to the efforts of the <a href="http://debian-live.alioth.debian.org/">Debian Live</a> 
	 project, we have created live CDs with experimental versions of KDE 4.</p>
	 <p>These live CDs allow users to try the latest KDE 4 without any risk their existing installation.</p>

	 <h3>Technical details</h3>
	 
	 <p><b>login</b>: user
	 <br>
	 <b>password</b>: live</p>
	 <p>If you do not use an English keyboard layout, you can specify another layout by passing the following option to the boot prompt:
	 <pre>live keyb=fr</pre></p>
	 
	 <p>Change "<code>fr</code>" to your ISO language code ("<code>de</code>" for German, "<code>es</code>" for Spanish, and so on.)</p>
	 
	 <p>For more information on options for the Live CD, see <a href="http://live.debian.net/other/manpages/live-initramfs.7.html">the live-initramfs manual page</a>.</p>

